            >
            has increased since its war in Ukraine. While the Russian military
            bases in Libya can help destabilize NATO‚Äôs Western flank, the
            security-for-resource agreements with Mali and Central Africa
            provide the Kremlin with mining concession agreements. Russia is
            also dependent on Africa for its resources, including precious
            metals and hydrocarbons.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            <strong>The warning:</strong> The US has warned that Russia may
            cooperate with China to open multiple conflicts, forcing the Western
            powers to split their attention and stretch resources. Officials
            warn that Russian proxy forces could target NATO assets. They also
            warned about the spread of disinformation and proxy narratives
            across Africa.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            The NATO commander emphasized preparedness for simultaneous
            conflicts in Europe and the Pacific, forecasting coordinated attacks
            by Russia and China as early as 2027.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            <strong>The impact:</strong> Western powers have imposed sanctions
            on Wagner-linked companies and officials, but that has had minimal
            effect on the Russian operations. Putin‚Äôs Africa strategy
            encompasses ‚Äålow-cost, high-impact support that will help it achieve
